wT4dNHyFW3ClTLe0em-VV6FXg=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvZmV0Y2gvd180MjQsY19saW1pdCxmX2F1dG8scV9hdXRvOmdvb2QsZmxfcHJvZ3Jlc3NpdmU6c3RlZXAvaHR0cHMlM0ElMkYlMkZzdWJzdGFjay1wb3N0LW1lZGlhLnMzLmFtYXpvbmF3cy5jb20lMkZwdWJsaWMlMkZpbWFnZXMlMkZiNjQ0ODg5MS04MGZkLTQ0NmEtYjczOS1iYjcyYjE4NmY4NGNfMTAzMHg2MzAucG5n 424w, https://reader.miniflux. 848w, https://reader.miniflux. 1272w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/lo1mf- 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"/></picture></a><figcaption>Tweet, exhibit GX-751</figcaption></figure><blockquote><p>AUSA: Is it a real number?</p><p>Wang: No.</p><p>AUSA: So it’s a fake number?</p><p>Wang: Yes.</p><p>AUSA: Was the real number higher or lower than the fake number?</p><p>Wang: Lower.</p></blockquote><p>Code snippets shown to the jury demonstrated how Nishad Singh wrote some code that would update the insurance fund amount by adding to it the daily trading volume, multiplied by a randomish number around 7,500, and dividing it by a billion, thus making it appear as though the website was referencing a real account balance that was fluctuating as the exchange added funds or withdrew from it to cover losses. In reality, it was all made up.</p><figure><a href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F33b15ea1-a6e3-4342-9410-34f8eea18393_1444x1146.png" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/uRDIt9yBLXSN8aMfsMUd7jf30gC8_ 424w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/9_yNkVVr9gXtX_ 848w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/5kYUUVns5GpG7rQZQ3wsBnm4K__fPK-giHrJBDftgP0=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvZmV0Y2gvd18xMjcyLGNfbGltaXQsZl93ZWJwLHFfYXV0bzpnb29kLGZsX3Byb2dyZXNzaXZlOnN0ZWVwL2h0dHBzJTNBJTJGJTJGc3Vic3RhY2stcG9zdC1tZWRpYS5zMy5hbWF6b25hd3MuY29tJTJGcHVibGljJTJGaW1hZ2VzJTJGMzNiMTVlYTEtYTZlMy00MzQyLTk0MTAtMzRmOGVlYTE4MzkzXzE0NDR4MTE0Ni5wbmc= 1272w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/hPm_RvAVrdRboaHk1JTXhLvdMe_Z3Gtu6QoJjoc_x6E=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvZmV0Y2gvd18xNDU2LGNfbGltaXQsZl93ZWJwLHFfYXV0bzpnb29kLGZsX3Byb2dyZXNzaXZlOnN0ZWVwL2h0dHBzJTNBJTJGJTJGc3Vic3RhY2stcG9zdC1tZWRpYS5zMy5hbWF6b25hd3MuY29tJTJGcHVibGljJTJGaW1hZ2VzJTJGMzNiMTVlYTEtYTZlMy00MzQyLTk0MTAtMzRmOGVlYTE4MzkzXzE0NDR4MTE0Ni5wbmc= 1456w" sizes="100vw"/><img src="https://reader.miniflux." alt="Github diff showing addition of code:  def _get_change()-&gt; Decimal:     daily_volume = current_session().query(func.sum(Trade.size * Trade.price)).filter(         Trade.created_at &gt; datetime.now() - timedelta(days=1)).scalar() or Decimal()         return f2d(numpy.random.normal(7500, 3000))* daily_volume / Decimal(&#39;1e9&#39;)  @always_run_in_transaction(ro=False) def update_public_insurance_fund():     change = _get_change() sess = current_session() +     public_insurance_fund = Public InsuranceFund.get(sess)  sess.add(Public InsuranceFundChange(public_insurance_fund-public_insurance_fund, size-change))     public_insurance_fund.size += change     sess.commit()" title="Github diff showing addition of code:  def _get_change()-&gt; Decimal:     daily_volume = current_session().query(func.sum(Trade.size * Trade.price)).filter(         Trade.created_at &gt; datetime.now() - timedelta(days=1)).scalar() or Decimal()         return f2d(numpy.random.normal(7500, 3000))* daily_volume / Decimal(&#39;1e9&#39;)  @always_run_in_transaction(ro=False) def update_public_insurance_fund():     change = _get_change() sess = current_session() +     public_insurance_fund = Public InsuranceFund.get(sess)  sess.add(Public InsuranceFundChange(public_insurance_fund-public_insurance_fund, size-change))     public_insurance_fund.size += change     sess.commit()" srcset="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/JPVCoZqQOyWedZi4EfbZuuwSm1B4ANVUmHP8YE7_1pA=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvZmV0Y2gvd180MjQsY19saW1pdCxmX2F1dG8scV9hdXRvOmdvb2QsZmxfcHJvZ3Jlc3NpdmU6c3RlZXAvaHR0cHMlM0ElMkYlMkZzdWJzdGFjay1wb3N0LW1lZGlhLnMzLmFtYXpvbmF3cy5jb20lMkZwdWJsaWMlMkZpbWFnZXMlMkYzM2IxNWVhMS1hNmUzLTQzNDItOTQxMC0zNGY4ZWVhMTgzOTNfMTQ0NHgxMTQ2LnBuZw== 424w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/yYppFB-9diGz- 848w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/X9plYdrbdsZr2ht-QTp- 1272w, https://reader.miniflux. 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"/></picture></a><figcaption>From exhibit <a href="https://mollywhite.net/storage/sbf-trial/GX-600.pdf" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">GX-600</a>. The falsified account balance change is primarily calculated in line 19.</figcaption></figure><p>This is pretty damning. One could possibly explain away an inaccurate number — say, one that was hardcoded into the website and never changed to reflect the true fund balance — by saying that they had   correctly represented it at one point in time and forgot to change it. But it’s really hard to come up with a good explanation for why the fund was being incremented by a <em>random</em> fluctuating number that was in no way tied to any actual account balance, besides the obvious: that FTX was trying to present a falsified but convincing number to customers. That would be fraud.</p><p>Elsewhere in the code, it’s possible to observe that the amount of FTT in the fund was actually represented by a hardcoded value in the user interface, and was not pulling from an external datasource to get a real number. </p><figure><a href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F44f41549-76a4-4aa3-96cd-de22f5319e15_1414x1742.png" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/KY8dQSd81RncMTOYOX- 424w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/p2_NzUwTNtjKQBe_Gk0PsB- 848w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/cZcSYHZ_ckty- 1272w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/lqturCgKTOw6RLsM3LvY4Yb13XhTyDX4pHp_Qfz2X68=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvZmV0Y2gvd18xNDU2LGNfbGltaXQsZl93ZWJwLHFfYXV0bzpnb29kLGZsX3Byb2dyZXNzaXZlOnN0ZWVwL2h0dHBzJTNBJTJGJTJGc3Vic3RhY2stcG9zdC1tZWRpYS5zMy5hbWF6b25hd3MuY29tJTJGcHVibGljJTJGaW1hZ2VzJTJGNDRmNDE1NDktNzZhNC00YWEzLTk2Y2QtZGUyMmY1MzE5ZTE1XzE0MTR4MTc0Mi5wbmc= 1456w" sizes="100vw"/><img src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/zdKAwt1c6ha3EksnbNYgDPetp2dmI7_wcui_-Fs3I9U=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvZmV0Y2gvd18xNDU2LGNfbGltaXQsZl9hdXRvLHFfYXV0bzpnb29kLGZsX3Byb2dyZXNzaXZlOnN0ZWVwL2h0dHBzJTNBJTJGJTJGc3Vic3RhY2stcG9zdC1tZWRpYS5zMy5hbWF6b25hd3MuY29tJTJGcHVibGljJTJGaW1hZ2VzJTJGNDRmNDE1NDktNzZhNC00YWEzLTk2Y2QtZGUyMmY1MzE5ZTE1XzE0MTR4MTc0Mi5wbmc=" alt="function InsuranceFundInformation() {   let insuranceFund = useData(&#39;/stats/insurance_fund&#39;);   let classes = useStyles();   if (!insuranceFund) {     return null;   }   return (     &lt;Card className={classes.card}&gt;       &lt;CardContent&gt;         &lt;Typography variant=&#34;h5&#34; gutterBottom&gt;           &lt;Trans&gt;Insurance Fund&lt;/Trans&gt;         &lt;/Typography&gt;         &lt;Typography&gt;           &lt;Trans&gt;             Size: {{ usdSize: coinSizeFormat.format(insuranceFund.size) }} USD,{&#39; &#39;} {{ fttSize: coinSizeFormat.format(5250000) }} FTT           &lt;/Trans&gt;         &lt;/Typography&gt;       &lt;Typography&gt;         &lt;Trans&gt;           Last updated: {{ lastUpdated: new Date(insuranceFund.updatedAt).toLocaleString() }}         &lt;/Trans&gt;       &lt;/Typography&gt;       &lt;/CardContent&gt;     &lt;/Card&gt;   ); }" title="function InsuranceFundInformation() {   let insuranceFund = useData(&#39;/stats/insurance_fund&#39;);   let classes = useStyles();   if (!insuranceFund) {     return null;   }   return (     &lt;Card className={classes.card}&gt;       &lt;CardContent&gt;         &lt;Typography variant=&#34;h5&#34; gutterBottom&gt;           &lt;Trans&gt;Insurance Fund&lt;/Trans&gt;    